26:42.080 --> 26:43.439
Who's he?!

26:43.440 --> 26:45.639
Plumber. Oh, I need
some comfort, Sue.

26:45.640 --> 26:48.199
My daughter's in prison.
I'm a broken woman.

26:48.200 --> 26:52.199
You think sharing a room
with Tutankhamun Does Deep Throat
is making my day?

26:52.200 --> 26:54.679
Why not you stay, too?

26:54.680 --> 26:58.679
Ugh!

27:02.000 --> 27:05.999
Is this where you keep
your little stopcock?

27:10.880 --> 27:12.399
Up your arse!

27:12.400 --> 27:15.999
Marty! Oh, Marty! Thank God!

27:16.000 --> 27:19.999
I've got something for you.

27:31.500 --> 27:33.499
Kev set it up on the internet.

27:33.500 --> 27:36.339
So, we drove over, but as soon
as we handed the money to

27:36.340 --> 27:38.419
the orphanage owner, we got raided.

27:38.420 --> 27:40.579
Shit.

27:40.580 --> 27:44.219
Veronica grabbed the baby and
stuffed him in the car with me,

27:44.220 --> 27:48.219
but the cops grabbed 'em. Veronica
was yelling, "drive, fuck off!

27:48.300 --> 27:52.059
"Fucking drive", so I did!
I drove off and left 'em.

27:52.060 --> 27:54.059
Fucking turncoat!

27:54.060 --> 27:56.819
You would've been
nicked if you hadn't.

27:56.820 --> 27:58.259
I didn't know what to do.

27:58.260 --> 28:02.259
I was too scared to drive the car
back so I hitched.

28:05.820 --> 28:07.499
Fuck it!

28:07.500 --> 28:09.579
(BABY CRIES)

28:09.580 --> 28:12.379
Stolen baby!

28:12.380 --> 28:16.379
TYRES SQUEAL

28:19.700 --> 28:22.779
Fuck it!

28:22.780 --> 28:26.779
(BABY CRYING)

28:26.900 --> 28:29.739
When did you last sleep, Marty?

28:29.740 --> 28:31.579
Dunno.

28:31.580 --> 28:33.699
Why won't he stop crying?

28:33.700 --> 28:35.779
I haven't hurt him, have I?

28:35.780 --> 28:37.499
So what are you gonna do?
Are you gonna keep it?

28:37.500 --> 28:39.259
Course not.I want to.

28:39.260 --> 28:42.819
Debbie?

28:42.820 --> 28:45.219
What's going on with
all that crying?!

28:45.220 --> 28:49.099
It's Katie. She doesn't like
having strangers in the house.

28:49.100 --> 28:51.579
I am not a stranger, Debbie.

28:51.580 --> 28:55.579
And I do not appreciate you putting
my cashmere jumper on a boil wash!

28:57.300 --> 28:58.859
Is that not what it goes on?

28:58.860 --> 29:02.859
I don't know how much longer I
can put up with this, Debbie.

29:04.940 --> 29:06.499
He's stopped crying.

29:06.500 --> 29:08.019
He likes you.

29:08.020 --> 29:09.299
No, he doesn't!

29:09.300 --> 29:12.539
Yeah, he does! Look.

29:12.540 --> 29:14.259
See?

29:14.260 --> 29:15.579
He wants you to be his mum.

29:15.580 --> 29:19.579
Marty! You're being insane!

29:40.060 --> 29:41.979
All right, Frank?

29:41.980 --> 29:45.459
Monica!

29:45.460 --> 29:49.459
We've got some catching up to do.

29:51.780 --> 29:53.619
Who'd have thought it eh, Frank?

29:53.620 --> 29:57.259
Little Lip, 19,
you and me grandparents.

29:57.260 --> 30:00.259
We don't seem old enough, do we?

30:00.260 --> 30:02.259
He's had it easy, though, in't he?

30:02.260 --> 30:05.459
I mean kids these days,
they don't know they're born.

30:05.460 --> 30:07.939
When I was Lip's age, I'd done time,
got crabs,

30:07.940 --> 30:10.539
knocked up sixgirls,
fought off bailiffs.

30:10.540 --> 30:13.779
Not many kids these days
can say that, can they?

30:13.780 --> 30:16.099
Remember when we met, Frank?

30:16.100 --> 30:18.619
1979, Ripper year.

30:18.620 --> 30:21.339
They had you in four times.

30:21.340 --> 30:23.379
They had you in four times.
God, like it was yesterday.

30:23.380 --> 30:26.339
Thought you'd stood me up,
thought you weren't interested.

30:26.340 --> 30:28.539
Me? No, course I was!

30:28.540 --> 30:31.859
Then I proposed to you.
Outside Aytoun dole office.

30:31.860 --> 30:33.899
Thought I was up the duff.

30:33.900 --> 30:37.899
Never thought you'd say yes,
but you did.

30:39.380 --> 30:41.179
And we got married.

30:41.180 --> 30:43.579
So, have the kids said
anything to you about,

30:43.580 --> 30:46.419
you know, eh, Sheila and me?

30:46.420 --> 30:47.699
Sheila?

30:47.700 --> 30:51.539
Yeah.What sort of thing?

30:51.540 --> 30:53.779
I do!

30:53.780 --> 30:56.659
I never got the divorce through
from Monica in the end,

30:56.660 --> 30:58.419
so it's not legal anyway.

30:58.420 --> 31:00.499
Anyway, I better go

31:00.500 --> 31:04.459
and get the twins from Debbie.
Don't want to take advantage.

31:04.460 --> 31:06.979
Actually, Frank,
I think I'll come with you.

31:06.980 --> 31:09.339
I'd like to see where
you live properly.

31:09.340 --> 31:11.419
Yeah, but the thing is,

31:11.420 --> 31:15.419
you know, it's, you know, Sheila,
me girlfriend, she'll probably...

31:15.620 --> 31:19.619
Yeah, but she's away doing a cookery
course, isn't she? Kids told me.

31:19.700 --> 31:23.699
Well, yeah, but she just probably
wouldn't in, in effect, but she...

31:23.860 --> 31:26.259
Come on.See ya.

31:26.260 --> 31:27.979
Sue, please?

31:27.980 --> 31:29.979
We'd be a proper family.

31:29.980 --> 31:31.779
I don't know what that is, Marty!

31:31.780 --> 31:33.659
We don't know anything
about looking after a baby!

31:33.660 --> 31:35.499
But we could learn.

31:35.500 --> 31:39.499
And then there's thepolice,
social services.

31:39.900 --> 31:42.259
Look, Kev and Veronica bought him.

31:42.260 --> 31:44.579
Someone else would.
You could sell him.

31:44.580 --> 31:47.419
What, on eBay?

31:47.420 --> 31:51.379
All right, leave him at maternity!
They'll take care of him.

31:51.380 --> 31:55.339
You've got my number, Pawel.

31:55.340 --> 31:57.379
Ooh, what a man!

31:57.380 --> 31:59.459
Big hands, he had, did you see?

31:59.460 --> 32:02.699
Saucy bugger!

32:02.700 --> 32:04.379
Oh, my God, Marty!

32:04.380 --> 32:07.659
Oh, thank the Good Lord!

32:07.660 --> 32:09.619
I've been beside meself!

32:09.620 --> 32:12.779
You've no idea what you've put me...

32:12.780 --> 32:14.699
Tell me you didn't bring that back.

32:14.700 --> 32:17.419
Yeah, I have. Your grandson.

32:17.420 --> 32:19.579
He's no grandson of mine!

32:19.580 --> 32:21.939
People'll think I have
foreign blood in me!

32:21.940 --> 32:23.619
You didn't seem to mind last night.

32:23.620 --> 32:25.659
He's from Basingstoke!

32:25.660 --> 32:28.339
Mum, I want to keep him.
You'll help me, won't you?

32:28.340 --> 32:31.219
Marty Fisher, you
can't even keep a job!

32:31.220 --> 32:33.139
And she's no better!

32:33.140 --> 32:34.459
I'm not getting involved.

32:34.460 --> 32:38.459
She's right. I'm sorry, Marty,but
for once, me and your mum agree.

32:40.620 --> 32:42.459
Sorry, Billy.

32:42.460 --> 32:44.539
KLAXON

32:44.540 --> 32:48.539
Oh, Norma!

32:51.820 --> 32:55.819
Someone to see you, Mum.

32:56.500 --> 32:57.539
Norma.

32:57.540 --> 33:00.019
Oh, well I'll...

33:00.020 --> 33:03.459
What d'you think you're doing?
