37:26.740 --> 37:30.739
Debbie...

37:31.500 --> 37:33.019
I'm sorry, Marty!

37:33.020 --> 37:37.019
You're my friend andI've
done something horrible!

37:38.780 --> 37:42.779
It's OK, it's OK.

37:44.780 --> 37:46.339
I know you didn't mean it.

37:46.340 --> 37:50.339
Fucking bitch!

37:50.380 --> 37:52.619
It'll be all right.

37:52.620 --> 37:56.619
Marty,
you're gonna have to go, mate.

37:57.940 --> 38:01.939
It'll be all right.

38:02.740 --> 38:04.819
Marty? >

38:04.820 --> 38:07.459
Don't abandon him.

38:07.460 --> 38:10.099
Please.

38:10.100 --> 38:14.099
Marty, come on!
Stan'll be back any minute.

38:19.460 --> 38:21.939
Oh, my children!

38:21.940 --> 38:24.939
Why is God punishing me?!

38:24.940 --> 38:28.939
It's all right, Carol. We're not
gonna throw you out just cos the
rest of your family's gone.

38:36.420 --> 38:39.339
See you later.

38:39.340 --> 38:42.059
Ha! Gotcha! Don't need a
warrant out here, do I?!

38:42.060 --> 38:43.099
Sue!Marty!

38:43.100 --> 38:44.099
Sue!

38:49.180 --> 38:50.819
Romanian coppers are on their way.

38:50.820 --> 38:54.819
But it's not the baby they want!
Pants on fire!

38:55.300 --> 38:59.299
Oh, for Pete's sake! Is there not
a WPC in here anywhere?

39:00.780 --> 39:02.339
Who are you?

39:02.340 --> 39:04.939
I'm the baby's mother.
Can I have him please, Stan?

39:04.940 --> 39:05.459
What you talking about?!

39:05.460 --> 39:07.099
PC Waterman!

39:07.100 --> 39:10.099
Yeah, PC...
But you haven't got a baby, Sue!

39:10.100 --> 39:12.299
What's this then, blow-up monkey?

39:12.300 --> 39:16.019
Hello. Aw, come here... He's hungry.

39:16.020 --> 39:17.699
He wants his mummy...

39:17.700 --> 39:21.299
Is she lying?
She's lying, isn't she?

39:21.300 --> 39:25.299
If that's your baby,
then where's its birth certificate?

39:25.340 --> 39:27.379
Here.

39:27.380 --> 39:31.299
Oh... sorry.

39:31.300 --> 39:34.139
You don't think I'd do this
if he wasn't mine, do you?

39:34.140 --> 39:35.459
Suck a tit!

39:35.460 --> 39:36.659
Now look, Sue.
We know that baby's stolen so.

39:36.660 --> 39:38.419
No, he's not!

39:38.420 --> 39:42.419
And even if he was, he's an orphan,
so you can't send him back to...

39:43.340 --> 39:44.979
I didn't know he was an orphan!

39:44.980 --> 39:45.499
That's not the point, PC O'Leary!

39:45.500 --> 39:48.379
But it is.

39:48.380 --> 39:51.019
I know what that's like.

39:51.020 --> 39:54.739
I never even knew me mam and dad!
It's fucking awful!

39:54.740 --> 39:58.419
We can't send him back!

39:58.420 --> 39:59.699
Please Stan?

39:59.700 --> 40:03.699
Piss in your tea!

40:10.020 --> 40:14.019
Save the baby?

40:15.020 --> 40:19.019
Well, it looks like we must've
made a terrible mistake then.

40:32.100 --> 40:34.059
So are we really
gonna keep him, then?!

40:34.060 --> 40:37.339
We have to do it properly though
Marty. I'm not living with your mum.

40:37.340 --> 40:37.899
Slag.

40:37.900 --> 40:41.099
And we need the proper stuff.
I'm not slumming it.

40:41.100 --> 40:44.099
We'll need a three-wheel baby buggy,
proper car seat...

40:44.100 --> 40:45.819
We have to get a car first!

40:45.820 --> 40:48.539
A nice one. And I was thinking maybe
then we could adopt another one.

40:48.540 --> 40:49.139
Hey?

40:49.140 --> 40:51.139
Well, child benefit's 70 a month,

40:51.140 --> 40:52.499
per child. Oooh!

40:52.500 --> 40:54.059
What's the matter?

40:54.060 --> 40:56.539
Nothing, just a bit of
morning sickness, I think.

40:56.540 --> 41:03.659
So, if we had four, that would be
280. If we had six, that would 670.

41:03.660 --> 41:04.179
Say what you said before?

41:04.180 --> 41:05.459
Morning sickness.

41:05.460 --> 41:06.979
Does that mean me spunk works?!

41:06.980 --> 41:08.419
(LAUGHS)

41:08.420 --> 41:09.459
I don't believe it!

41:09.460 --> 41:13.459
Marty!

41:15.100 --> 41:17.339
What you doing with her?! Get out!

41:17.340 --> 41:20.659
She's just brought her back, Lip.
She had her for the afternoon.

41:20.660 --> 41:23.739
She's my granddaughter.
You can't stop me from seeing her,

41:23.740 --> 41:25.499
it'd break me heart!
I'm begging you...

41:25.500 --> 41:28.139
It's not her fault you had
a row with Paddy, is it?

41:28.140 --> 41:29.939
Don't punish her for it.

41:29.940 --> 41:32.579
Three visits a week.
That's all I want.

41:32.580 --> 41:35.179
You don't interfere though.

41:35.180 --> 41:39.059
Hey, what's the matter?

41:39.060 --> 41:41.219
What the fuck is that?!

41:41.220 --> 41:43.019
Sweet, isn't it?

41:43.020 --> 41:44.539
Ahhh...

41:44.540 --> 41:48.539
TATTOOIST NEEDLE WHIRRS

41:49.500 --> 41:53.499
I didn't tell her she could do it.

42:01.460 --> 42:05.459
Sorry about that
little interruption...

42:05.700 --> 42:07.499
Ooh, dear!

42:07.500 --> 42:11.499
Oh, yeah. Just some kids. Threw
something through the letterbox.
Cunts.

42:12.860 --> 42:15.819
No, they didn't.
You set fire to your dinner.

42:15.820 --> 42:17.179
No!

42:17.180 --> 42:18.859
They told me at the hospital.

42:18.860 --> 42:20.939
They couldn't get hold of your wife,

42:20.940 --> 42:22.819
Sheila Gallagher.

42:22.820 --> 42:25.979
So they had to get hold of your ex.

42:25.980 --> 42:27.859
How do you think that
made me feel,

42:27.860 --> 42:30.659
knowing that
I'm still married to you?

42:30.660 --> 42:31.979
I want you back Frank.

42:31.980 --> 42:33.019
PHONE RINGS

42:33.020 --> 42:34.859
That's why I'm here.

42:34.860 --> 42:36.379
I want my old life back.

42:36.380 --> 42:38.899
Let me just...

42:38.900 --> 42:40.979
Hello?

42:40.980 --> 42:43.459
'Hiya, love.'

42:43.460 --> 42:45.659
Oh, hiya, Sheila.

42:45.660 --> 42:47.019
'Is there something wrong?'

42:47.020 --> 42:48.819
What?

42:48.820 --> 42:50.339
'You don't sound yourself.'

42:50.340 --> 42:51.739
No, no, I'm fine, I'm fine.

42:51.740 --> 42:53.379
'Nothing's happened has it?'

42:53.380 --> 42:55.539
What round here.
Must be joking ain't you.

42:55.540 --> 42:56.939
Same old, same old, innit.

42:56.940 --> 42:57.979
'Guess what happened...'

42:57.980 --> 42:59.659
'Guess what happened...'
(You and me.)

42:59.660 --> 43:00.979
What?

43:00.980 --> 43:01.499
What?
'Frank?'

43:01.500 --> 43:03.619
What?
'Frank?'
No, no... what?

43:03.620 --> 43:05.099
(You and me.)

43:05.100 --> 43:06.499
'Is there someone there?'

43:06.500 --> 43:10.379
No, no, it's just a...
no, it's just a soap on the telly.

43:10.380 --> 43:12.379
I dropped the phone.

43:12.380 --> 43:16.379
'Is it that time already?
My cinnamon swirls will be burnt.'

43:18.380 --> 43:22.099
Yeah, so, er...
so when is it that you coming back?

43:22.100 --> 43:23.979
'Tomorrow, love.'

43:23.980 --> 43:25.139
Tomorrow.

43:25.140 --> 43:26.179
'It's Monday.'

43:26.180 --> 43:30.179
Is it?

43:33.020 --> 43:35.859
Look Debs,

43:35.860 --> 43:39.859
we want you to decide
if Mum stays or not.

43:40.940 --> 43:43.379
Just say the word.

43:43.380 --> 43:47.379
And she's gone.

43:53.620 --> 43:56.179
And you'll go?

43:56.180 --> 44:00.179
If I tell you to?

44:22.460 --> 44:26.459
I need to get the dinner on.

44:48.260 --> 44:49.899
So you're off then, are you?

44:49.900 --> 44:51.619
Am I fuck!

44:51.620 --> 44:55.299
You might have come over all Stepford
Wives, but I'm not falling for it.

44:55.300 --> 44:58.419
I'm stopping right here
till you come to your senses!

44:58.420 --> 45:02.419
Right where I can see you.

45:02.860 --> 45:06.859
Oh, squatters' rights,
European Rules!

45:17.740 --> 45:20.659
'Surprises come in lots of
different shapes and sizes.

45:20.660 --> 45:23.979
'There's the good ones like finding
out you've passed your maths exam

45:23.980 --> 45:27.379
'even though the calculator ran
out three seconds after you've

45:27.380 --> 45:31.059
'started the test and finding a pound
down the back of the sofa.

45:31.060 --> 45:35.059
'Then there's the bad ones
like being called to casualty
cos your youngest brother's allergic

45:35.620 --> 45:38.779
'to the trifle you just made him.
Or discovering that the rash

45:38.780 --> 45:42.779
'you'd finally thought had gone
has come back double and it's not

45:43.780 --> 45:47.179
'going away no matter how hard
you scratch it. And realising

45:47.180 --> 45:49.699
'that it's not a rash it's an
infection or worse a melanoma.

45:49.700 --> 45:53.699
'You can try ignore it, but someday
soon it's gonna jump up and bite ya.'

46:40.180 --> 46:41.339
G'night, Carl.

46:41.340 --> 46:43.539
Good night, Mum.

46:43.540 --> 46:44.659
G'night, Ian.

46:45.660 --> 46:46.659
Goodnight, Mum.

46:47.160 --> 46:51.159
G'night, Debbie.

46:52.680 --> 46:54.919
G'night, Phillip.

46:54.920 --> 46:58.159
He can't HEAR you,
he's in the next house!

46:58.160 --> 47:00.279
G'night, Liam.

47:00.280 --> 47:05.279
Will you lot shut the fuck up
and go to fucking sleep
before I crown the lot of you!

